175":"1175","1142":"1142","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","about 1144":"oko 1144.","Scotland":"Škotska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"about 1144–":"okolo 1144–Zesnulý","1140–1238":"1140–1238","1142–Male":"1142–Zesnulý","1144–Male":"1144–Zesnulý","1175–Male":"1175–Zesnulý","1100–1174":"1100–1174","1100–Female":"1100–Zesnulá","1238":"1238","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1175":"1175","1142":"1142","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","about 1144":"okolo 1144","Scotland":"Skotsko, United Kingdom"},"da":{"about 1144–":"omkring 1144–Afdød","1140–1238":"1140–1238","1142–Male":"1142–Afdød","1144–Male":"1144–Afdød","1175–Male":"1175–Afdød","1100–1174":"1100–1174","1100–Female":"1100–Afdød","1238":"1238","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1175":"1175","1142":"1142","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","about 1144":"omkring 1144","Scotland":"Skotland, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"about 1144–":"circa 1144–Overleden","1140–1238":"1140–1238","1142–Male":"1142–Overleden","1144–Male":"1144–Overleden","1175–Male":"1175–Overleden","1100–1174":"1100–1174","1100–Female":"1100–Overleden","1238":"1238","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1175":"1175","1142":"1142","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","about 1144":"circa 1144","Scotland":"Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1144–":"about 1144–Deceased","1140–1238":"1140–1238","1142–Male":"1142–Deceased","1144–Male":"1144–Deceased","1175–Male":"1175–Deceased","1100–1174":"1100–1174","1100–Female":"1100–Deceased","1238":"1238","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1175":"1175","1142":"1142","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","about 1144":"about 1144","Scotland":"Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"McGregor","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Griogair</b> or <b>Mac Greagair</b> ‘son of <i>Griogar</i>’, Gaelic form of the personal name   Gregory  . Compare   Grierson  .","History: The Scottish Highland clan McGregor claims descent from the king of Picts and Scots Kenneth MacAlpin (Cináed mac Ailpín; 810–858  AD ). The origins of the clan are unclear. In the 13th century it was established on lands on the shores of Loch Awe and already in conflict with its neighbors of Clan Campbell. By the 16th century the McGregors had retreated deep into Glen Strae and acquired the nickname ‘Children of the Mist’. In 1603 the clan was abolished by royal edict and many members of the clan changed their surname. A year later, the chief of Clan McGregor and eleven of his followers were hanged in Edinburgh. Despite the proscription, the clan survived and supported the king in the Scottish Civil War (1644–51). The exploits of the Jacobite leader Rob Roy McGregor (1671–1734) were romanticized in a novel by Sir Walter Scott. The proscription was eventually repealed in 1774."],"variants":[{"name":"Gregory","meanings":["English (of Norman origin) and French: from a personal name that was popular throughout Christendom in the Middle Ages. The Greek original, <i>Grēgorios</i>, is a derivative of <i>grēgorein</i> ‘to be awake, to be watchful’. However, the Latin form, <i>Gregorius</i>, came to be associated by folk etymology with <i>grex</i>, <i>gregis</i> ‘flock, herd’, under the influence of the Christian image of the good shepherd. The Greek name was borne in the early Christian centuries by two fathers of the Orthodox Church, Saint Gregory Nazianzene (<i>c.</i> 325–390) and Saint Gregory of Nyssa (<i>c.</i> 331–395), and later by sixteen popes, starting with Gregory the Great (<i>c.</i> 540–604). It was also the name of 3rd- and 4th-century apostles of Armenia. In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed many cognates from other languages, e.g. Italian   Gregorio  , German, Slovak, and Slovenian   Gregor  , Polish <b>Grzegorz</b>, Czech <b>Řehoř</b> (see   Rehor  ), and French   Gregoire  , and also their patronymics and other derivatives, e.g. Polish   Grzegorczyk  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When McGregor Bishop of Inverness was born about 1144, in Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Malcolm MacGregor 8th Lord of Glenorchy, was 45 and his mother, Majorie Fitz Duncan, was 45. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1144–":"umbes 1144–Surnud","1140–1238":"1140–1238","1142–Male":"1142–Surnud","1144–Male":"1144–Surnud","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1100–1174":"1100–1174","1100–Female":"1100–Surnud","1238":"1238","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1175":"1175","1142":"1142","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","about 1144":"umbes 1144","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1144–":"noin 1144–Kuollut","1140–1238":"1140–1238","1142–Male":"1142–Kuollut","1144–Male":"1144–Kuollut","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","1100–1174":"1100–1174","1100–Female":"1100–Kuollut","1238":"1238","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1175":"1175","1142":"1142","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","about 1144":"noin 1144","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1144–":"environ 1144–Décédé","1140–1238":"1140–1238","1142–Male":"1142–Décédé","1144–Male":"1144–Décédé","1175–Male":"1175–Décédé","1100–1174":"1100–1174","1100–Female":"1100–Décédée","1238":"1238","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1175":"1175","1142":"1142","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","about 1144":"environ 1144","Scotland":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque McGregor Bishop of Inverness est né environ 1144, à Écosse, Royaume-Uni, son père, Sir Malcolm MacGregor 8th Lord of Glenorchy, avait 45 ans et sa mère, Majorie Fitz Duncan, avait 45 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"about 1144–":"um 1144–Verstorben","1140–1238":"1140–1238","1142–Male":"1142–Verstorben","1144–Male":"1144–Verstorben","1175–Male":"1175–Verstorben","1100–1174":"1100–1174","1100–Female":"1100–Verstorben","1238":"1238","1100":"1100","1144":"1144","1175":"1175","1142":"1142","1174":"1174","1140":"1140","about 1144":"um 1144","Scotland":"Schottland, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Als McGregor Bishop of Inverness um 1144 in Schottland, United Kingdom geboren wurde, war sein Vater Sir Malcolm MacGregor 8th 